  "text": "The intra-feature sharing of the covariance function, mean function, and hyperparameters is intended to capture the idea that the characteristic variations of features will tend to be consistent across members of the set. If a feature function learns to capture, for example, whether or not users in a collaborative filtering problem enjoy Christmas movies, then we might expect them to share an annual periodic variation. The inter-feature covariance matrix Σ U , on the other hand, captures the idea that some features are informative about others and that this information can be shared. [CITATION_1] applied this idea to scalar features.",
